Polysphincta organensis

sp. nov. can be distinguished from other species of the 

P. dizardi

species-group by the combination of the following characters: (1) epomia absent (Fig. 
6B
); (2) malar space 0.4 times as long as proximal mandibular width (Fig. 
6B
); (3) fore wing vein 1 
cu-a
interstitial relative to 
M&RS
(Fig. 
6A
); (4) mesosoma orange with weak spot posteriorly in metapleuron and posterior carinae of propodeum brown (Fig. 
6A
); (5) wings hyaline (Fig. 
6A
); (6) hind leg whitish with inner region of coxa, trochanter proximally, trochantellus distally, femur proximally and distally, tibia proximally and distally, first tarsal segment distally, and remaining tarsal segments entirely blackish brown (Fig. 
6A
); (7) metasoma blackish with anterior margin centrally orange in tergite I, tergites II-VI with anterior and anterolateral margins whitish (Fig. 
6A, C, G
); (8) ovipositor slightly slender, 1.2-1.3 times as long as hind tibia.
